<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Ptilophora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ptilophora jezoensis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jezoensis">Ptilophora jezoensis</taxonomicName>
without any explanation. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kishida, Y" journalOrPublisher="Tinea" pageId="2" pageNumber="71" pagination="86 - 91" title="Two new species of the genus Ptilophora (Lepidoptera, Notodontidae) from China." volume="17" year="2002">Kishida and Kobayashi (2002)</bibRefCitation>
revalidated it as a species. It belongs to the plumigera group, based on the round valva in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
